-- Tiernan-Locke Wins Tour of Britain, First Home Champ Since 1993
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-09-16T15:57:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-16/tiernan-locke-wins-tour-of-britain-first-home-champ-since-1993.html
Jonathan Tiernan-Locke won the Tour
of Britain, becoming the first home cyclist to clinch the title
in 19 years.  Mark Cavendish  of Britain won today’s eighth and final
stage over 91.2 miles in a sprint finish in Guildford, south of
London. It was his third stage victory in this year’s race.  Tiernan-Locke took an 18-second lead into today’s stage and
finished in the main group of riders.  The last British winner of the race was Chris Lillywhite in
1993.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 